body:
I cannot find an equivalent to verilog testbench, for truth-table verification.
Suppose I  want to verify an and gate :

```
module and(input a, intput b, output o)
  assign o = a & b;
endmodule
```
I have to write the following code

```
int main(int argc, char **argv)
{
  Verilated::commandArgs(argc, argv);
  Vand  *test = new Vand;
  
  test->a = 0;
  test->b = 0;
  test->eval();
  assert(test->o == 0);
  //here goes the 3 other cases...
  test->eval();
  assert(test->o == 1);

  return 0;
}
```

But if inputs/outputs names or count changes, I have to rewrite the whole testbench. Maybe it could be beneficial to have access to inputs/outputs as an array :

```
int main(int argc, char **argv)
{
  Verilated::commandArgs(argc, argv);
  Vand  *test = new Vand;
  
  bool inputs[][] = {{0, 0}, {0, 1}, {1, 0}, {1, 1}};
  bool output[] = {0, 0, 0, 1}
  
  for(int i = 0; i < 4; i++)
  {
    test->inputs = inputs[i];
    test->eval();
    assert(*test->outputs == output[i]);
  }
  return 0;
}
```

There may be a way to do that, but I could not find any searching the doc or the source code.
